<main class="landing">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero__copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Phase 7 · Agentic Neon</p>
      <h1>Agentic Dev Stacks</h1>
      <p class="lede">AI-ready development machines with curated profiles, agents, and MCP toolchains. Built for dark mode, fast onboarding, and a confident handover to production.</p>
      <div class="hero__actions">
        <a class="button button--primary" href="{{{relativize 'golden-path.html'}}}">Golden paths</a>
        <a class="button button--ghost" href="{{{relativize 'vscode/packs.html'}}}">Stack catalogue</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hero__panel">
      <div class="panel__title">Quick start</div>
      <ul class="panel__list">
        <li><span class="chip chip--cyan">JS/TS</span><code>bash scripts/install/fullstack-js-ts-macos.sh</code></li>
        <li><span class="chip chip--violet">Python</span><code>bash scripts/install/python-data-analytics-macos.sh</code></li>
        <li><span class="chip chip--amber">Infra/SRE</span><code>bash scripts/install/infra-ops-sre-macos.sh</code></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="panel__hint">Use the OS-specific install script, then import the matching VS Code profile export.</p>
      <a class="text-link" href="{{{relativize 'stack-catalogue.html'}}}">View full stack catalogue</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-gallery">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Stack gallery</p>
      <h2>Curated stacks with matching agents</h2>
      <p class="section-lede">Pick a persona, pull the devcontainer, and keep MCP + Copilot agents aligned with the repository’s single source of truth.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="stack-grid">
      {{> stack-card
        stackId="fullstack-js-ts"
        name="Fullstack JS/TS"
        persona="Product engineers building web and API surfaces"
        languages="Node · TypeScript · React-ready"
        agents="refactor-surgeon · test-writer · doc-surgeon"
        installScript="bash scripts/install/fullstack-js-ts-macos.sh"
        docHref=(relativize 'vscode/packs.html')
      }}
      {{> stack-card
        stackId="python-data-analytics"
        name="Python Data & Analytics"
        persona="Data/ML engineers building pipelines and notebooks"
        languages="Python · notebooks · data viz"
        agents="data-explorer · pipeline-refactorer · doc-surgeon"
        installScript="bash scripts/install/python-data-analytics-macos.sh"
        docHref=(relativize 'vscode/packs.html')
      }}
      {{> stack-card
        stackId="infra-ops-sre"
        name="Infra / Ops / SRE"
        persona="Platform and incident engineers"
        languages="Terraform · Kubernetes · CLI-first"
        agents="infra-reviewer · incident-scribe · doc-surgeon"
        installScript="bash scripts/install/infra-ops-sre-macos.sh"
        docHref=(relativize 'vscode/packs.html')
      }}
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="golden-cards">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Golden paths</p>
      <h2>High-trust workflows ready to run</h2>
      <p class="section-lede">Opinionated flows for agent-driven delivery. Each path links to commands, prompts, and review guardrails.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="info-card">
        <p class="info-card__eyebrow">Engineering</p>
        <h3>JS/TS refactor + tests</h3>
        <p class="info-card__body">Scoped refactors with inline tests, test-writer agent, and MCP-backed code search.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="{{{relativize 'golden-path.html#js-ts-refactor-tests'}}}">Run the flow</a>
      </article>
      <article class="info-card">
        <p class="info-card__eyebrow">Data</p>
        <h3>Data pipeline hardening</h3>
        <p class="info-card__body">Stabilise ETL with pipeline-refactorer, notebook validation, and observability prompts.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="{{{relativize 'golden-path.html#data-pipeline-hardening'}}}">See steps</a>
      </article>
      <article class="info-card">
        <p class="info-card__eyebrow">Reliability</p>
        <h3>Incident review + postmortem</h3>
        <p class="info-card__body">Infra-reviewer + incident-scribe, with MCP read-only defaults and timelines auto-sketched.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="{{{relativize 'golden-path.html#incident-review-postmortem'}}}">View outline</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="landing-docs">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Documentation</p>
      <h2>Inside the docs</h2>
      <p class="section-lede">Read the guardrails before enabling agents or MCP servers. Everything stays declarative and reproducible.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-grid">
      <article class="docs-card">
        <h3>Codex configuration</h3>
        <p>Safe vs danger modes, MCP wiring, and how to merge UI fragments without touching dotfiles.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="{{{relativize 'codex/config-guides.html'}}}">Config guides</a>
      </article>
      <article class="docs-card">
        <h3>Agent roster</h3>
        <p>Custom Copilot agents, MCP tool access, and prompts that ship with each stack.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="{{{relativize 'agents/agents-overview.html'}}}">Browse agents</a>
      </article>
      <article class="docs-card">
        <h3>MCP provisioning</h3>
        <p>Bootstrap manifests, read-only defaults, and validation commands for server fragments.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="{{{relativize 'mcp-provisioning.html'}}}">Provision MCP</a>
      </article>
    </div>
    <div class="article-preview">
{{{page.contents}}}
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
